</p>

<h2>What if I lost the toothbrush packaging to mail back?</h2>
<p>
  As long as you have already entered one code from your Preserve toothbrush package (mail back packages only) and have received a postage paid label, simply print out the label and follow the instructions for mailing using a 16 oz. plastic beverage bottle.  This way you’re sending both a bottle and your toothbrushes for recycling! All of this is explained once you enter your code, but simply put all you need to do is:
</p>
<ul>
  <li>Put between 2 and 6 toothbrushes in a dry 16 oz, plastic bottle with the label removed</li>
  <li>Roll the mailing label so you can insert it into the bottle</li>
  <li>Insert the toothbrushes and twist on the cap</li>
</ul>
<p>
  Make sure that the label can be read from the outside of the bottle.  You can then mail it at any USPS mailbox.  If you don’t have a plastic beverage bottle you can use a lightweight sturdy envelope.
</p>

<h2>What if I want to mail back more than two toothbrushes for recycling and I don’t have a water bottle?</h2>
<p>
  We chose the water bottle as a way to return multiple toothbrushes because it is lightweight, widely available, and easy to recycle once received!  However, any lightweight, sturdy envelope is also acceptable when sending in your Preserve toothbrushes for recycling.
</p>

